"title": "6233: rejection, human experience of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6233: rejection, human experience of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Feelings of rejection by God may be a result of alienation caused directly or indirectly by sin. God's people also experience rejection by a hostile world. Experiences and feelings of rejection are to be met with prayer, forgiveness and perseverance, together with confidence in God's commitment to and compassion for, his people.</p>\n<h2>Feelings of rejection by God</h2>\n<h3>Feelings of national rejection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:1\">PSA 74:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:14\">ISA 49:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:9\">PSA 44:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:11\">PSA 108:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:27\">ISA 40:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:17\">JER 13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:9\">JER 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:2\">LAM 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:20\">LAM 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:11\">EZK 37:11</a></p>\n<h3>Feelings of personal rejection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps13:1\">PSA 13:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a> <em>Jesus Christ experiences separation from his Father as a consequence of bearing human sin.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1-Ps22:2\">PSA 22:1–22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps43:2\">PSA 43:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:14\">PSA 88:14</a></p>\n<h2>God's servants experience rejection</h2>\n<h3>Samuel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:5-1Sam8:7\">1SA 8:5–8:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Elijah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:10\">1KI 19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:22\">1KI 18:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:1-1Kgs19:4\">1KI 19:1–19:4</a></p>\n<h3>The psalmist</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:7\">PSA 41:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:6-Ps22:8\">PSA 22:6–22:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:12-Ps31:13\">PSA 31:12–31:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:20\">PSA 69:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:10\">PSA 71:10</a></p>\n<h3>Jeremiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:10\">JER 15:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:7-Jer20:9\">JER 20:7–20:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:14-Jer20:15\">JER 20:14–20:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:18\">JER 20:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:5\">ISA 53:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:11\">JHN 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:18\">LUK 23:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:18\">JHN 15:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:10-Matt5:11\">MAT 5:10–5:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:22\">LUK 6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:14\">JHN 17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:50\">ACT 13:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:19\">ACT 14:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:22\">ACT 16:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:12\">2TI 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:12\">1PE 4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Responding to rejection</h2>\n<h3>Appealing to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:42\">2CH 6:42</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:9\">PSA 27:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:12\">PSA 71:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:9-Ps22:11\">PSA 22:9–22:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:19-Ps22:21\">PSA 22:19–22:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:23-Ps44:24\">PSA 44:23–44:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:11-Ps51:12\">PSA 51:11–51:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:7-Ps77:12\">PSA 77:7–77:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:10\">PSA 132:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:15\">JER 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:12\">JER 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:21-Lam5:22\">LAM 5:21–5:22</a></p>\n<h3>Offering forgiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:17\">GEN 50:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:16\">2TI 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Rejoicing in suffering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:11-Matt5:12\">MAT 5:11–5:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:22-Luke6:23\">LUK 6:22–6:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:41\">ACT 5:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:3\">ROM 5:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:2-Jas1:3\">JAS 1:2–1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Persevering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:28-Acts5:29\">ACT 5:28–5:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a></p>\n<h2>Encouragement for those experiencing rejection</h2>\n<h3>God's commitment to his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15-Isa49:16\">ISA 49:15–49:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:10\">PSA 27:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:14\">PSA 94:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:20\">JER 31:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:21-Lam3:24\">LAM 3:21–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1-Hos11:4\">HOS 11:1–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:30-Matt10:31\">MAT 10:30–10:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:7\">LUK 12:7</a></p>\n<h3>God's compassion and forgiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:31-Lam3:32\">LAM 3:31–3:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:36\">DEU 32:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:7-Ps130:8\">PSA 130:7–130:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa12:1-Isa12:2\">ISA 12:1–12:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:13\">ISA 49:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:25\">EZK 39:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:8-Hos11:9\">HOS 11:8–11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:7-2Cor2:8\">2CO 2:7–2:8</a> <em>God's readiness to forgive is to be reflected in the attitude of his people towards one another.</em></p>\n<h3>God's strengthening</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:28-Isa40:31\">ISA 40:28–40:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:17\">2TI 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>God's vindication of his people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:14\">PSA 135:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:6-Isa50:9\">ISA 50:6–50:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:17\">ISA 54:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:18\">ROM 8:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:13\">1PE 4:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Support from fellow believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:4\">2CO 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:22\">ACT 14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:6-2Cor6:7\">2CO 6:6–6:7</a></p>",
